UML:TaggedValue.value: Decoupling: No a priori agreement required between Service Providers and Service Requesters
Available services can be queried and listened to
Semantic Service consumption: Requesters specify the semantics of the requested service, rather than specifying its syntax
Distribution and heterogeneity of Service Providers and Service Requesters hidden from the involved parties by the buses architecture
Scripting Domain Specific languages facilitate programmers productivity and are especially effective for small tasks, such composing several services, with simple control and data flow
